{"segment_id": "00374", "page_num": 374, "segment": "company tweaks and tests enrollment even as site traffic grows modestly.\nBy the end of the month, the site is converting 8.2% of its 1,462 visitors.\n\nFigure 28-1. Can you see the gradual improvement in\nthis chart?\n\nThe question is: should this company keep working on enrollment, or has it\nhit diminishing returns? By applying a trend line to the conversion rate, we\ncan quickly see the diminishing returns (Figure 28-2).\n\nFigure 28-2: Maybe 9% is as good as this will get\nwithout a radical change\n\nUltimately, the best the company will be able to do with all else being equal\nis achieve a conversion rate of around 9%. So on the one hand, that’s a\ngood baseline, and gives a sense of the universe it’s in. On the other hand,\nall else is seldom equal. A new strategy for user acquisition could change\nthings significantly.\n\n348\n\nPArt tHree: LIneS In tHe SAnD", "source_file": "Lean_Analytics.pdf", "extraction_method": "pdfminer", "ocr_used": false, "has_table": false, "chapter_num": "26", "chapter_title": "USer-generAteD Content: LIneS In tHe SAnD", "section_num": null, "section_title": null, "l1_summary": "By applying a trend line to the conversion rate, we\ncan quickly see the diminishing returns (Figure 28-2). Figure 28-2: Maybe 9% is as good as this will get\nwithout a radical change Ultimately, the best the company will be able to do with all else being equal\nis achieve a conversion rate of around...", "l2_summary": "company tweaks and tests enrollment even as site traffic grows modestly. The question is: should this company keep working on enrollment, or has it\nhit diminishing returns? By applying a trend line to the conversion rate, we\ncan quickly see the diminishing returns (Figure 28-2). Figure 28-2: Maybe 9% is as good as this will get\nwithout a radical change Ultimately, the best the company will be able to do with all else being equal\nis achieve a conversion rate of around 9%. On the other